---
description: Overall project architecture and conventions
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---
- This is a Next.js app router project with Supabase auth and Drizzle ORM.
- All database tables live in a Postgres schema defined by the DATABASE_SCHEMA env var. Never use the public schema.
- Use Server Actions for all data mutations. Do not create API routes for CRUD operations.
- Use Drizzle ORM for all database queries. Never use raw SQL or the Supabase client for data access.
- Use the Supabase client only for authentication operations.
- All pages under /dashboard are protected and require authentication.
